						<summary>

						<p>A sculptured stone (fifth) set up near the tank bund.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to about the 9th century A.D., on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record the death of a warrior, Rudramanṟu who was a servant of Ugrampuli, in a fight.</p>						

						</summary>
